Type: Package
Package: concstats
Title: Market Structure, Concentration and Inequality Measures
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person(given = "Andreas",
           family = "Schneider",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "schneiderconsultingpy@gmail.com",
           comment = c(ORCID = "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5630-1097"))
Description: Based on individual market shares of all participants in a
    market or space or their respective sales figures, the package offers
    a set of different structural and concentration measures frequently -
    and not so frequently - used in research and in practice. Measures can
    be calculated in groups or individually. The calculated measure or the
    resulting vector in table format should help practitioners make more
    informed decisions. Methods used in this package are from:
    O. C. Herfindahl (1950), "Concentration in the steel industry (PhD thesis)";
    A. O. Hirschmann (1945), "National power and structure of foreign trade";
    C. E. Shannon (1948), "A Mathematical Theory of Communication";
    J. G. Palma (2006), "Globalizing Inequality: 'Centrifugal' and 'Centripetal'
    Forces at Work" <https://www.un.org/esa/desa/papers/2006/wp35_2006.pdf>;
    A. Cobham and A. Summer (2013), "Is It All About the Tails? The Palma
    Measure of Income Inequality"
    <https://www.cgdev.org/sites/default/files/it-all-about-tails-palma-measure-income-inequality.pdf>;
    R. Ginevicius and S. Cirba (2009), "Additive measurement of market
    concentration" <doi:10.3846/1611-1699.2009.10.191-198>;
    E. J. Chang, S. M. Guerra, R. A. de Souza Penaloza, and B. M. Tabak (2005)
    "Measuring Banking concentration: the Brazilian case";
    P. Garcia Alba Idunate, P. (1994), "Un Indice de dominancia para el
    analisis de la estructura de los mercados"
    <https://www.jstor.org/stable/20856736>;
    A. Melnik, O. Shy, and R. Stenbacka (2008), "Assessing market dominance"
    <doi:10.1016/j.jebo.2008.03.010>
